&lt;Microelectronics and ComputerTechnology Corp> said its board approved a restructuring of itsadvanced computer architecture program.    The private sector cooperative research venture, which isowned by 20 U.S. companies, said the restructuring is based ona study by its technical advisory board. The study occurred dueto changing requirements, the company said.    Formerly comprised of four separate projects, the programwill now have a central resaerch core and three laboratoriescalled satellites. The work in the core program will focus onlong-range research, the company said. Reuter&#3;